<p>I am applying the <a href="https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/examples/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/examples/mllib/LDAExample.scala" rel="nofollow">MLlib LDA example</a> on various corpora downloaded from <a href="http://corpora2.informatik.uni-leipzig.de/" rel="nofollow">enter link description here</a> I am filtering out the stopwords, and also excluding the very frequent terms and the very rare terms. The problem is that I am always having topics that have very similar profile.</p>  <p>Here is an example of the topics I am getting, by running the algorithm on a corpora of 300K english sentences from Wikipedia (eng_wikipedia_2010_300K-sentences), knowing that I am having similar behaviour when using other corpora:</p>  <pre><code>TOPIC 0 dai 0.0020492776129338083 call    0.0019627409470977355 citi    0.0019496273507300062 three   0.0019172201890256511 gener   0.0018325842193426059 plai    0.0018287121439402873 peopl   0.001786839660855886 well    0.0017792000702589461 system  0.0017410979899730565 area    0.001721711978388363 power   0.0016906026954800833 forc    0.0016646631729486227 number  0.0016343386030518979 1   0.0016238591786476033 team    0.0016112030952801443 second  0.0015692071709961662 develop 0.0015670177558504078 group   0.0015378927495689552 unit    0.001535180513974118 nation  0.001520548489788889  TOPIC 1 dai 0.002027230927747474 call    0.0019861147606781222 citi    0.0019793753441068825 three   0.0019315799215582723 gener   0.0018482143436741026 plai    0.0018088629290540156 peopl   0.0017929339168126625 well    0.0017549252518608278 system  0.0016936542725510587 power   0.0016792684719108006 area    0.0016604962232717288 forc    0.0016575624332970456 1   0.0016344588453542676 number  0.0016147026427518426 team    0.0015914797457267642 develop 0.001580085843019015 unit    0.0015659585445574969 nation  0.0015412334667742672 second  0.0015292625574896467 group   0.0015111594105132022  TOPIC 2 dai 0.002028407701986021 call    0.00198